The paper discusses the concept of Aeronautical Ad Hoc Networking (AANET) for providing broadband communications above clouds, which involves wireless networking among commercial passenger airplanes. This topic falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the challenges and solutions related to network scheduling and routing, security, interference, and optimization, which are relevant to Information Theory (cs.IT), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Multiagent Systems (cs.MA), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
